Package ca.queensu.cs.cisc124.notes.generics.basics

Interface Queue<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of the elements in the queue
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayQueue, LinkedQueue
    public interface Queue<E>
    The Queue interface represents a first-in-first-out (FIFO) queue of elements. In addition to the usual enqueue and dequeue methods, this interface allows the user to get the number of elements in a queue, query if the queue is empty, and get the first and last elements of the queue without modifying the queue.
